# Data Access Patterns

## Data Fetching — Server Components Only

All data retrieval must happen in Server Components. Never fetch data on the client.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — fetch in a Server Component
export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  const decks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));
  return <DeckList decks={decks} />;
}

// ❌ BAD — fetching in a Client Component
"use client";
useEffect(() => {
  fetch("/api/decks").then(...);
}, []);
```

## Mutations — Server Actions Only

All inserts, updates, and deletes must go through Server Actions. Never mutate via API routes or client-side calls.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
"use server";
export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) { ... }

// ❌ BAD — mutation in a route handler or client fetch
export async function POST(req: Request) {
  await db.insert(decks).values(...);
}
```

## Validation — Zod Required

All data passed into Server Actions must be validated with Zod before any database operation.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
import { z } from "zod";

const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  description: z.string().optional(),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = createDeckSchema.safeParse(input);
  if (!parsed.success) return { error: parsed.error.flatten() };
  // proceed with db operation
}

// ❌ BAD — no validation, or using FormData as the type
export async function createDeck(data: FormData) { ... }
```

## Rules

- Data fetching belongs in Server Components — not `useEffect`, not `fetch()` calls in client code
- Mutations belong in Server Actions — not route handlers or client-side code
- Every Server Action must define a typed input schema using Zod (`z.infer<typeof schema>`)
- Never use `FormData` as a Server Action parameter type
- Always call `safeParse` or `parse` before touching the database
